I'm honestly not sure what pre-existing license these mods would apply for (especially `Fix-Stutter`), but I still wanna write a License or Terms and Agreements section of some sort so people don't think they can just do *literally anything* with my mods/code

YOU ARE ALLOWED TO DO THE FOLLOWING WITH THESE SCRIPTS AND CODE:
- Redistribute the code for non-commercial purposes
- Edit and make any changes to the code
- Install the software on any device
- Create forks of the repo, including going offsite from github
- Suggest and submit pull/commit requests to this repo
- Port the code/scripts to any game
- Use code as a reference for making your own mods/code
- Feature the mod/code in Video/Image/Article content, regardless of commercial use (this will be considered fair use)

YOU ARE NOT ALLOWED TO DO THE FOLLOWING:
- Redistribute, Fork or Edit the code while removing/not including credit to the original developer (ILC)
- Redistribute the code for commercial purposes or any monetary purposes
- Claim that you or someone else created/developed the mod that's not mentioned on the page or commit logs (Mention of mod/tool developers that helped influence THPS4 modding are an exception)
- Claim that you are the sole developer of the code just because a pull request or bug report was merged/solved

FIX-STUTTER IS A REDISTRIBUTION OF 1.9z-binkw32.dll, INCLUDED IN THIS REPO FOR THE SAKE OF CONVIENCE. LINK TO SOURCE: https://github.com/vogonsorg/radgametools
